    "title": "Hiring Medical Officer at Aravind Eye Hospital",
    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Aravind Eye Hospital. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Medical Officer to strengthen our Howrah-based team.\n\nAbout Aravind Eye Hospital:\nAravind Eye Hospital is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Howrah, West Bengal, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Aravind Eye Hospital!",
